00:13:49,340 --> 00:13:53,220
给她戴上这么漂亮的戒指 是一项明智之举 奥斯威勒先生
Very wise to put such a nice ring on her finger, Mr. Osweiller.

172
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:54,970
我们有多久没举办过婚礼了 
When was the last time we had a wedding?

173
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:57,180
这可是大事情
This is quite the occasion.

174
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:59,100
或许正是列车此刻所需要的
Perhaps just the occasion the train needs.

175
00:13:59,180 --> 00:14:01,020
不 我们没想大肆操办
No, we're not expecting anything.

176
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:02,600
-我们甚至都不… -我想
- We don't even-- - I am.

177
00:14:02,690 --> 00:14:06,320
你应该办一场大婚礼 亲爱的 人生的这一程太艰苦了
And you should, my dear. Life's been so bloody dreary this leg.

178
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,530
我们会允许所有人都歇一个班次
We'll give everyone a shift off.

179
00:14:08,610 --> 00:14:11,570
提醒一下那些抱怨的人 团结是什么样子的
Let's remind all the grumblers what unity looks like.

180
00:14:11,650 --> 00:14:15,370
提醒他们我们是同一列列车上的 忠诚会得到回报
That we're all in this together, and loyalty is rewarded.

181
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:16,990
你觉得怎么样 
- What do you think?

182
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:18,660
稍微歇口气对大家有好处
- We could all use a little respite.

183
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:21,540
-或许可以多分一两份口粮… -太好了 那就定在明天
- Maybe an extra ration or-- - Wonderful. Tomorrow then.

184
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:23,290
明天 
Tomorrow?

185
00:14:23,380 --> 00:14:25,960
是呀 有何不可 没时间临阵退缩
Yeah. Why not? No time for cold feet.

186
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:27,880
LJ 我们要让夜车焕然一新
We'll transform the Nightcar, LJ.

187
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:30,590
或者我该称呼你为 “奥斯威勒太太” 
Or should I say, Mrs. Osweiller?

188
00:14:31,340 --> 00:14:32,680
弗尔杰-奥斯威勒 
- Oh… Folger-Osweiller? - Um…

189
00:14:33,340 --> 00:14:37,060
非常顺口 我要用层层的红色天鹅绒来布置
Rolls off the tongue. I'm seeing red velvet, layers.

190
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:40,060
扎拉 去找糕点师
Ah… Zarah, go see the Cakemaker.

191
00:14:40,140 --> 00:14:43,650
-你把糕点师贬入堆肥区了 -那就把他弄出来 我们要举办婚礼
- You put the Cakemaker in Compost. - Then get him out. We're getting married.

192
00:14:46,980 --> 00:14:48,320
（忠臣大婚 ）

193
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:51,440
给他冲个澡 他做糕点需要什么 就去面包房拿 明白吗 
Get him a shower and anything he needs from the bakery, okay?

194
00:14:51,530 --> 00:14:53,610
谢谢
Thank you. Thank you.

195
00:14:58,660 --> 00:15:00,160
（全列车公假）

196
00:15:02,710 --> 00:15:04,370
你在这里干什么 
What the hell are you doing here?

197
00:15:04,870 --> 00:15:07,590
威尔福德在造武器 你知道这事吗 
Wilford's building a weapon. You know anything about that?

198
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:10,090
我知道他在策划什么 但不知道武器的事
I know he's up to something, but no.

199
00:15:10,170 --> 00:15:14,630
鲁丝看到哈维在制造那个武器 所以她想跟他取得联系
Well, Ruth saw Javi working on it, so she wants to make contact with him.

200
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:17,550
我告诉过你们了 哈维不愿跟我说话
I told you guys, Javi won't talk to me.

201
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:19,760
自从被那只狗咬过之后 他整个人就变了
He hasn't been the same since that dog attack.

202
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:24,810
谁没个伤疤呢  这是鲁丝的决定 她想见他
Well, we all got scars. It's Ruth's call. She wants to see him.

203
00:15:35,860 --> 00:15:39,700
砸显示器也不会让卫星与地球同步
Hitting the monitor does not tend to affect the satellite's geosync.

204
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:43,750
但能让我感觉好受些 不过我们大家都不在状态
What it does do is make me feel better, but we're all falling out of orbit.

205
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:46,790
本 我们要怎么在大海里捞到针呢 
How do you find a needle in a haystack?

206
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:48,920
谢天谢地 只是一片大海而已
Thank God, it's only a haystack.

207
00:15:49,670 --> 00:15:52,170
-你有什么见解吗  -只有一个
- You have any theories? - I have one theory.

208
00:15:53,010 --> 00:15:54,220
他在跟踪我们 
That he is following us?

209
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:58,680
这一心理假设真不错啊
That's a pretty good psychological assumption.

210
00:16:01,970 --> 00:16:06,060
我们将在一天左右回到主轨道 经过这里时
If he is following us, we're back on the main line in a day or so.

211
00:16:06,850 --> 00:16:10,230
我们的卫星覆盖范围会有所改善 如果他在跟踪我们
As we came through here, our satellite coverage improved.

212
00:16:11,150 --> 00:16:12,440
或许我们就能探测到他
Maybe we see him then.

213
00:16:13,110 --> 00:16:14,110
他也能探测到我们 
And he sees us?

214
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:19,030
你妈妈要是看到你昨天 驾驭列车时的表现 会很骄傲的
Your mum would be proud of how you handled the train yesterday.

215
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:22,330
我并不这么认为 本 不过谢谢你这么说
I don't really think so, Ben, but thank you.

216
00:16:22,410 --> 00:16:24,790
艾莉 我们找到了一个幸存者
Alex, we found a survivor.

217
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:27,620
也许希望出现奇迹并无不可
Maybe we can hope for a miracle.

218
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:32,250
她已经死了 本
She's gone, Ben.

219
00:16:33,210 --> 00:16:34,710
我可以接受
It's all right.

220
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:12,420
嘿
Hey.

221
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:14,750
跟我说说她是谁
Tell me who she is.

222
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:20,220
至少告诉我你在找什么
At least tell me what you're looking for.

223
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:21,260
（沙特阿拉伯 苏丹）

224
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:42,200
你找到了什么 
What did you find?

225
00:17:43,530 --> 00:17:47,580
（又做了一个梦）

226
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:00,260
就在这里
Just, uh, in here.

227
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:03,390
（乘务员）

228
00:18:03,470 --> 00:18:05,010
我为你布置了一下
I've made it up for you.

229
00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:10,390
真暖和啊
It's, uh… It's so warm.

230
00:18:14,270 --> 00:18:16,730
-谢谢你… -我叫乔西
- Thank you, uh… - Josie.

231
00:18:16,820 --> 00:18:17,980
乔西
Josie. Josie.

232
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:22,660
不好意思 我已经很久没说话了
Sorry, it's, uh… It's been a long time since I spoke.

233
00:18:22,740 --> 00:18:24,700
没事 会慢慢熟练起来的
It's all right. It'll all come back.

234
00:18:26,870 --> 00:18:28,290
你活下来了 我的意思是…
You made it. I mean… Wow.

235
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:32,960
你没事吧 
You all right?

236
00:19:19,710 --> 00:19:20,670
嗨
Hey.

237
00:19:23,010 --> 00:19:24,300
你还好吗 
You all right?

238
00:19:26,510 --> 00:19:28,430
你离被冻死最近的一次有多近 
How close you ever come to freezing to death?

239
00:19:31,180 --> 00:19:33,060
跟多数人差不多吧
I guess no less than most of us.

240
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:35,520
那经历跟大家说的一样吗 
Is it like they say?

241
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:37,270
是的
Yeah.

242
00:19:39,190 --> 00:19:41,440
你开始放松 开始觉得暖和
You start to relax. It goes warm.

243
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:43,240
会看到一些东西
You see things.

244
00:19:44,110 --> 00:19:45,280
好吧
Okay.

245
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:47,700
比如说树 
Like, uh, trees?

246
00:19:47,780 --> 00:19:51,540
龙血树 青草
Dragon's blood tree. Grass.

247
00:19:52,950 --> 00:19:54,410
我能感觉到阳光
I could feel the sun.

248
00:19:56,540 --> 00:19:58,250
那是我们在找的地方
It was the place we're looking for.

249
00:20:00,290 --> 00:20:02,840
很高兴你活过来了 因为那不是我们在找的地方
Well, I'm glad you came back 'cause it wasn't.

250
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:06,260
不 听着 这种树只在亚丁湾生长
No, look, these trees only grow in the Gulf of Aden,

251
00:20:06,340 --> 00:20:09,970
亚丁湾就在阿拉伯暖点的中间
right here in the middle of our Arabian warm spot.

252
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:14,310
我以前从没听说过龙血树
I'd never even heard of a dragon's blood tree before,

253
00:20:15,020 --> 00:20:16,310
可我却看到了它
but I saw it.

254
00:20:18,020 --> 00:20:19,400
你是说你看到了未来 
Are you saying you had a vision?

255
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:22,730
-我只是在告诉你当时发生的事 -你告诉过别人吗 
- I'm just telling you what happened. - You tell anyone else?

256
00:20:22,820 --> 00:20:23,900
-没有 -很好
- No. - Good.

257
00:20:23,990 --> 00:20:25,530
保持正常状态
Keep it on the rails.

258
00:20:25,610 --> 00:20:29,160
你当时差点没命了 所以记忆中的某些东西闪现了出来
You had a close call, something popped out of your memory.

259
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:32,240
高中时学过的某种树
Some tree you learned about in high school.

260
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:37,210
是呀 你或许是对的 谢谢提点
Yeah. Yeah, you're probably right. Thanks.

261
00:20:37,290 --> 00:20:39,290
嗯 好
Yeah. Okay.

262
00:20:39,380 --> 00:20:42,170
和往常一样 又经历一次濒死体验 对吗 
Another day, another near-death experience, right?

263
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,170
好
Okay.

264
00:20:45,380 --> 00:20:46,840
-我爱你 哥们 -嗯
- Love you, buddy. - Yeah.

265
00:20:59,150 --> 00:21:01,310
凯文 今天我们的攻势与往日不同
We're on a different tack today, Kevin.

266
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,110
我们要发起魅力攻势
A charm offensive.

267
00:21:03,190 --> 00:21:04,280
你觉得怎么样 
What do you think?

268
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:06,490
太红了吗 
Too much red?

269
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,530
红色永不嫌够 先生
Never enough red, sir.

270
00:21:09,950 --> 00:21:10,780
我同意
I agree.

271
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:15,540
-你为什么要那么说  -说什么 
- Why'd you say that? - Say what?

272
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:18,250
我说什么了 
What?

273
00:21:18,330 --> 00:21:19,370
“弗尔杰-奥斯威勒”
"Folger-Osweiller."

274
00:21:20,580 --> 00:21:22,960
我只是那么一说而已 没想到他会记到登记簿上
I just said it. I didn't know he'd put it on the register.

275
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,920
是呀 这下他成了婚礼的主角
Yeah, well, it's his wedding now.

276
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,840
-我就知道他会这么做 -那又怎样 
- I knew he'd do this. - So what?

277
00:21:27,670 --> 00:21:30,130
这一天 我们将会享受 国王和王后的待遇
We get to be king and queen of everything for a day.

278
00:21:30,220 --> 00:21:31,720
他是在利用我们 LJ
He's using us, LJ.

279
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,300
他是在我们身上作投资
He's investing in us.

280
00:21:34,140 --> 00:21:36,560
办一场小小的仪式 我就很开心了
I would've been very happy with something small.

281
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:39,390
给你唱首歌 就几个朋友在场 但这是不可能的 对吗 
Sing you a song, a few of us. That wasn't on the table, was it?

282
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:41,850
没错 因为我们没有朋友
Yeah, because we don't have any friends.

283
00:21:41,940 --> 00:21:45,150
我希望我们成为大腕夫妇 有一天我们可能会管理这列列车
I wanna be in a power couple. We could run this train one day.

284
00:21:45,230 --> 00:21:47,110
-天啊 LJ  -怎么了 
- LJ, Jesus! - What?

285
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:50,780
年迈的人不断死去 都快没有年轻人了
Old people keep dying off, there's barely any young people left.

286
00:21:50,860 --> 00:21:53,030
很快 就得由我们来统领他们
And soon, we'll have to rule them.

287
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:56,990
这可是我们的婚礼啊 你就从不停止算计吗 
It's our wedding day. Do you ever stop conniving?

288
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:01,290
-算计是好事 -好吧 
- Conniving is good. - Fine!

289
00:22:01,370 --> 00:22:03,840
去算计吧 现在想取消已经太迟了
Connive away! It's too late to call it off now,

290
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:06,460
因为提出取消 威尔福德就会 把我的脑袋冻掉 对吗 
'cause Wilford would have my head out a port, wouldn't he?

291
00:22:06,550 --> 00:22:08,260
别这样甩手走开 
Don't walk away from me!

292
00:22:11,510 --> 00:22:12,590
奥斯 
Oz?

293
00:22:30,990 --> 00:22:31,900
哈维 
Javi?

294
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:44,920
哈维 
Javi?

295
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:50,300
你可以跟我说话的 这里没有别人
You can talk to me. No one is here.

296
00:22:56,220 --> 00:22:59,180
工程师 威尔福德要你去头等车厢
Engineer, Wilford wants you down in First.

297
00:22:59,270 --> 00:23:00,470
可我在上班呢
But I'm on shift.

298
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:04,940
我不知道 他要你去的 所以设成自动驾驶 快去就是
I don't know. That's what he wants, so put it on autopilot and off you go.

299
00:23:20,330 --> 00:23:21,910
你看上去很漂亮
You look beautiful.

300
00:23:22,750 --> 00:23:23,870
今天是你的大日子
- It's your big day. - Would you leave it?

301
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:25,250
你能别去管它了吗 
I don't care if it looks like shit. Just leave it.

302
00:23:26,250 --> 00:23:28,460
我不在乎它是否乱糟糟的 别去管它就是
Oh, dear. I heard the bride might be blue, but blue in the face?

303
00:23:28,540 --> 00:23:32,050
天啊 我听说过新娘子会有婚前忧郁 不知道还会大发脾气
Excuse me.

304
00:23:33,260 --> 00:23:35,640
-我先出去了 -好 那样最好 谢谢
Yes, that will be best, thank you.

305
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:41,060
好了 来 告诉我你在为什么生气
Now, now, here. Now, tell me what you fought about?

306
00:23:41,810 --> 00:23:45,980
“你总是在算计” 他觉得我又自私又冷酷
"You're always conniving." He thinks I'm selfish and I'm cruel.

307
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:48,900
有时候我不得不那样 不是吗 
I have to be sometimes, don't I?

308
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:53,240
所以我才想让你待在夜车上 LJ
It's why I wanted you in the Nightcar, LJ.

309
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:56,610
你是个现实主义者 你知道有人受伤是难免的事
You're a realist. You understand someone always gets hurt.

310
00:23:56,700 --> 00:24:01,080
就是 我虽然不会大声说出来 但“这就是生活”
Yes, it's like, I don't say it out loud, but c'est la vie.

311
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:04,410
他或许还觉得 整场婚礼都被我接管了
He also probably thinks I'm taking over the whole ceremony.

312
00:24:05,460 --> 00:24:08,460
你明白为什么 你们的婚礼对我很重要吗 
Do you understand why your wedding is important to me?

313
00:24:10,090 --> 00:24:11,670
能帮你管束大家
Helps keep everyone in line.

314
00:24:12,340 --> 00:24:15,630
没错 他们会看到 只有一种办事方法 就是我的方法
Yes. They see there's only one way, the way I do things.

315
00:24:17,010 --> 00:24:20,430
你看 在这列列车上 有一样东西
You see, on the train, the old laws and morality,

316
00:24:20,510 --> 00:24:23,930
比旧法和道德更重要 它是什么 
they don't matter as much as… what?

317
00:24:25,980 --> 00:24:27,560
-忠诚 -没错
- Loyalty. - That's right.

318
00:24:27,650 --> 00:24:29,520
对列车的忠诚
Loyalty to the train.

319
00:24:31,110 --> 00:24:35,030
好了 你这假惺惺的眼泪 留着到婚礼上流吧
Now, save the crocodile tears for the ceremony.

320
00:24:35,110 --> 00:24:36,860
为了我 好好表演一番
Make a show of it, for me.

321
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,120
我会的
I will.

322
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:42,330
回头见
See you soon.

323
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:55,210
婚床放在这里很不错呀
Lovely spot for your wedding bed.

324
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:01,430
谢谢夸奖 是我们自己布置的
Thank you. We, uh, did it ourselves.

325
00:25:03,180 --> 00:25:04,350
过来
Come.

326
00:25:04,430 --> 00:25:05,600
坐 来啊
Sit down. Come on.

327
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:13,980
年轻激昂的爱情 我很熟悉
Young, tumultuous love, I know it well.

328
00:25:15,190 --> 00:25:17,570
我指的是激昂的部分 我已经不再年轻了
Well, the tumultuous part, not the young bit anymore.

329
00:25:18,990 --> 00:25:20,660
不过 LJ不开心
But LJ's upset.

330
00:25:23,030 --> 00:25:24,240
是的 这个嘛…
Yeah, well, it's, uh…

331
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:27,120
是婚前紧张
Pre-wedding jitters.

332
00:25:27,870 --> 00:25:29,670
我们会没事的 是的
We'll be fine. Yeah.

333
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:33,000
我对她有很强的保护意识
Well, I am rather protective of her.

334
00:25:33,090 --> 00:25:38,760
所以 我好好查阅了一下 罗齐先生的人事记录
So I had a long look at Mr. Roche's personnel records,

335
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:42,090
你当制动员的时候 很会把握各种机会嘛
and you were an opportunistic boy in blue.

336
00:25:43,390 --> 00:25:45,640
我经营过几份副业 是的 先生
Well, ran a few side hustles. Yes, sir.

337
00:25:46,350 --> 00:25:48,930
一个劣迹斑斑的企业家
Ah, an entrepreneur with a vicious streak.

338
00:25:49,730 --> 00:25:51,650
这是当夜车经理的优良品质
Good qualities in a Nightcar manager.

339
00:25:54,110 --> 00:25:54,980
然而…
And yet…

340
00:25:57,190 --> 00:25:58,360
这双手…
these hands…

341
00:26:00,650 --> 00:26:02,620
