play piano so beautifully.

342
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:06,540
你心里有点渴望成为一名艺术家
Part of you just yearns to be an artiste,

343
00:26:07,540 --> 00:26:09,660
颤声吟唱最悲伤的歌曲
warbling the saddest of songs.

344
00:26:11,250 --> 00:26:15,460
我不是在所谓的 富有创造性的环境中长大的
Well, I didn't grow up in what you'd call a creative environment.

345
00:26:16,550 --> 00:26:17,920
你表达了自己的心声
You found your voice.

346
00:26:19,420 --> 00:26:20,420
钢琴师 
Piano man, hmm?

347
00:26:21,300 --> 00:26:23,510
你那红发妻子则负责吧台
And his ginger wife behind the bar.

348
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:28,310
你们是我的团队
You're my team here.

349
00:26:30,390 --> 00:26:31,520
这点我们明白
We understand that.

350
00:26:32,940 --> 00:26:33,940
真的
We do.

351
00:26:37,320 --> 00:26:39,940
你们制动员搜身的手法 还记得吗 
Your Brakeman shakedown move, remember?

352
00:26:40,860 --> 00:26:41,900
你也抓我的
Squeeze mine too.

353
00:26:42,860 --> 00:26:45,070
来吧 抓吧
Go on. Squeeze them.

354
00:26:46,530 --> 00:26:47,490
用力点
Harder.

355
00:26:48,580 --> 00:26:51,910
再用力点 用上所有的劲道
Harder. Give them some basso profundo.

356
00:26:53,830 --> 00:26:56,040
好 你的双手是用来干什么的 
Now, what are your hands for, hmm?

357
00:26:58,050 --> 00:26:59,460
捏碎别人的蛋
Crushing balls.

358
00:27:05,550 --> 00:27:07,510
还要用来爱抚你的妻子
And caressing your wife.

359
00:27:16,560 --> 00:27:20,650
在那之后 你想怎么弹琴都行
When that's done, by all means, tickle the ivories.

360
00:27:23,950 --> 00:27:25,570
因为你非常有才华
Because you're very talented.

361
00:27:27,830 --> 00:27:29,030
这是真心话
I mean that.

362
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:44,840
文件
Papers.

363
00:27:50,100 --> 00:27:51,100
包
Bag.

364
00:28:27,130 --> 00:28:28,050
德拉托尔先生
Mr. De la Torre.

365
00:28:28,930 --> 00:28:30,010
是我
Just me.

366
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:32,770
好久不见了
Long time no see.

367
00:28:33,350 --> 00:28:34,810
鲁丝 可你…
Ruth? But you…

368
00:28:35,850 --> 00:28:37,190
你应该在另一列列车上呀
You're on the other train.

369
00:28:37,270 --> 00:28:40,310
不 我一直都在这里 帮助乘客们
No, I've been here the whole time. I've been helping the passengers.

370
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:42,610
为我们在外面的朋友尽己所能
Doing my bit for our friends out there.

371
00:28:42,690 --> 00:28:43,900
你不该在这里的
You shouldn't be here.

372
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:48,360
哈维
Oh, Javi.

373
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,950
-我很抱歉… -不…
- Oh, I'm sorry-- - No, no, no…

374
00:28:53,660 --> 00:28:55,580
工程师 我只是要你帮忙 拜托了
Engineer, I just… I just need your help, please.

375
00:28:56,580 --> 00:28:59,790
你在列车后部做的那个东西 它是什么 它能做什么 
The thing that you're working on back there, what is it? What does it do?

376
00:29:00,750 --> 00:29:02,000
它能彻底阻止雷顿
It's gonna stop Layton dead.

377
00:29:03,840 --> 00:29:06,170
-我得回狗那里去了 抱歉 -不 先别走
- I need to go back to the dog, I'm sorry. - No, not yet.

378
00:29:06,260 --> 00:29:07,720
你得告诉我它是怎么运作的
Tell me how it works.

379
00:29:10,550 --> 00:29:13,310
-不  -哈维 哈维 
- No. No! No! - Javi? Javi!

380
00:29:27,700 --> 00:29:28,820
你美极了
Gorgeous.

381
00:29:42,590 --> 00:29:45,880
欢迎 勇敢的乘客们 工人们 及其他所有人
Welcome, brave passengers, workers, all now.

382
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:49,720
我很高兴大家能暂停手头的工作
It's my great pleasure to pause our labors,

383
00:29:50,840 --> 00:29:53,050
花点时间团聚在一起
and spend time in union.

384
00:29:53,140 --> 00:29:55,470
今天我们汇聚一堂 是为了庆祝
The union today by marriage,

385
00:29:56,640 --> 00:30:02,230
小莱拉弗尔杰 和约翰克里斯多夫奥斯威勒喜结良缘
of Lilah Folger Junior and John Christopher Osweiller.

386
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:13,530
我知道 最近这段行程 非常寒冷 供给不足
I know these have been cold miles of deprivation.

387
00:30:14,450 --> 00:30:16,160
纪律严酷
And discipline is harsh.

388
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:17,580
你们都得了冻疮
You've paid in frostbite,

389
00:30:18,830 --> 00:30:22,500
所爱的人因流感而丧生 愿他们安息
and loved ones lost to influenza. May they rest in peace.

390
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:27,920
所以 该是庆祝胜利的时候了 不是吗 
So it's time we celebrate a win, isn't it?

391
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:33,890
传统的婚姻
Old World matrimony.

392
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:38,470
各位 把酒杯倒满 我们有足够的酒 大家都有份
Everyone, fill a glass. There's enough for every soul.

393
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:40,100
还有额外的热餐
Extra hot food too.

394
00:30:40,770 --> 00:30:42,270
-我去去就回 -好
- I'll be back. - Okay.

395
00:30:42,350 --> 00:30:46,650
让全车上下 都为莱拉和约翰举起酒杯吧
Raise a glass up and down our train for Lilah and John.

396
00:30:46,730 --> 00:30:49,360
来吧 干杯
Come on. Cheers.

397
00:30:52,570 --> 00:30:53,450
现在 各位
Everyone now.

398
00:30:54,070 --> 00:30:56,740
再敬我们与列车牢不可破的协议
To our unbreakable pact with the train.

399
00:30:57,990 --> 00:30:59,040
敬忠诚
To loyalty

400
00:31:00,450 --> 00:31:02,250
以及你们与我的约定
and your contract with me.

401
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:05,290
生存
To survive.

402
00:31:08,380 --> 00:31:11,340
威尔福德 
Wilford! Wilford!

403
00:31:22,980 --> 00:31:25,850
听上去像是一种电磁脉冲武器
Sounds like an electromagnetic pulse weapon.

404
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:28,480
我从来没有真正见过
Never actually seen one before.

405
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:30,730
-但你知道它的运作原理吧  -知道
- But you do know how it works? - Yeah.

406
00:31:32,440 --> 00:31:37,200
它能发出电磁脉冲 破坏雪国列车上的所有电子设备
It sends out an electromagnetic pulse killing the electronics on Snowpiercer,

407
00:31:37,870 --> 00:31:39,240
让雷顿的列车无法前进
leaving Layton dead in the water.

408
00:31:39,330 --> 00:31:43,460
那趁着这场婚礼 我们来设法阻止那种情况发生
So while this wedding is happening, let's try and make it not do that.

409
00:31:43,540 --> 00:31:44,370
有操作手册吗 
- You got a manual?

410
00:31:44,460 --> 00:31:45,750
拜托 光明
- Come on, Lights.

411
00:31:45,830 --> 00:31:48,290
我跟鲁丝说你很擅长这类活儿
I told the lady you're good at this kind of thing.

412
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:50,500
解除电磁脉冲武器 
Disarming EMPs?

413
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:52,880
是呀
Yeah.

414
00:32:05,350 --> 00:32:06,350
干吗 
What?

415
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:09,480
哈维 你要去哪儿 
Where you going, Javi?

416
00:32:09,570 --> 00:32:10,650
回狗那里去
- Back to the dog. - Ah-ah.

417
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:13,690
你刚才去哪儿了 
Where are you coming from?

418
00:32:16,110 --> 00:32:17,490
收集最后一套数据
Final data collection.

419
00:32:18,370 --> 00:32:19,410
我能走了吗 
Can I go?

420
00:32:32,590 --> 00:32:33,710
跟我来
Come with me.

421
00:32:38,550 --> 00:32:39,550
跟着我
Follow me.

422
00:32:40,350 --> 00:32:41,390
你也是
You too.

423
00:32:43,890 --> 00:32:48,650
现在 我要你们完成
Now, I ask you to take the sacred steps

424
00:32:49,350 --> 00:32:52,020
与永恒机车相结合的神圣仪式
in union with the Eternal Engine.

425
00:32:53,940 --> 00:32:58,990
这四步代表了人类所经历的历程
These four steps represent the path humanity has taken.

426
00:33:02,030 --> 00:33:03,080
从青草
From grass

427
00:33:04,830 --> 00:33:05,910
到寒冰
to ice.

428
00:33:07,370 --> 00:33:09,750
-从寒冰到钢铁 -从寒冰到钢铁
- From ice to steel. - From ice to steel.

429
00:33:11,670 --> 00:33:13,710
从钢铁到…
And from steel to the lights…

430
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,470
永恒机车的灯光
of the Eternal Engine.

431
00:33:20,390 --> 00:33:22,140
有人来过这里吗 
Anyone come through here?

432
00:33:22,220 --> 00:33:24,220
那个被狗咬了脸的工程师常来这里
That dog-faced engineer's here all the time.

433
00:33:24,310 --> 00:33:25,770
不过他很快就会出来
But he's in and out.

434
00:33:25,850 --> 00:33:27,980
我们还是要进去看看
Well, we'll check it anyway.

435
00:33:29,190 --> 00:33:32,020
敌人会觉得这场婚礼 是他们行动的好时机 不是吗 
Wouldn't this wedding be a great distraction for the enemy?

436
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:42,700
我完全不知道要怎么解除这玩意儿
I have no idea how to disarm this thing.

437
00:33:42,780 --> 00:33:44,160
你就各处摆弄一下呗
Just start messing with it.

438
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:46,200
-这就是你的计划  -你才是我的计划
- That's your plan? - You're my plan.

439
00:33:49,790 --> 00:33:51,210
军靴和待客部的人来了 
Jackboots and teal coming!

440
00:33:51,290 --> 00:33:53,130
-什么  -我们会被困在这里的 快离开
- What? - They'll pin us back here. Let's go.

441
00:33:53,210 --> 00:33:54,710
我们得走了 快走
We gotta go. Let's go.

442
00:33:56,130 --> 00:33:58,090
-来呀 -不行 你们得继续解除武器
- Come on. - No. You need to keep working on it.

443
00:33:58,170 --> 00:33:59,340
你打算干什么 
What are you gonna do?

444
00:33:59,420 --> 00:34:03,010
我得去干扰他们 否则大家都会被困在这里
I'll need to run interference or we're all stuck back here.

445
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:05,310
如果他们看到了我 就不会进到这里来
They won't keep coming if they see me.

446
00:34:05,390 --> 00:34:08,480
只管解除这武器 给雷顿一个战斗机会
Just disable it, and give Layton a fighting chance.

447
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:10,810
-鲁丝… -派克先生 这是命令
- Ruth-- - That is an order, Mr. Pike.

448
00:34:12,270 --> 00:34:13,690
现在由你来负责了
You're in charge now.

449
00:34:15,650 --> 00:34:17,110
我信任你
I believe in you.

450
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:25,870
恭喜啊
Congratulations.

451
00:34:31,460 --> 00:34:32,620
真不错
That's nice.

452
00:34:46,100 --> 00:34:46,930
是你
You.

453
00:34:47,680 --> 00:34:49,430
没错 凯文 是我
Yes, Kevin. It's me.

454
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:52,810
你一直以来都在找的人
The one you've been looking for all this time.

455
00:34:54,310 --> 00:34:56,610
你像只没头苍蝇一样到处瞎找
Running around like a chicken with your head cut off.

456
00:34:56,690 --> 00:34:57,770
现在我来投降了
I'm surrendering.

457
00:34:58,780 --> 00:35:00,860
我又冷又饿 所以 动手吧
I'm cold and I'm starving. So, come on.

458
00:35:01,780 --> 00:35:04,320
不费吹灰之力 你就能当上英雄了
You get to be the hero without ever lifting a finger.

459
00:35:07,120 --> 00:35:08,200
把她带走
Take her.

460
00:35:33,140 --> 00:35:35,810
最初我们有34个人
There were 34 of us to start,

461
00:35:35,900 --> 00:35:38,610
依靠核电站的剩余电力竭力维持
eking it out on the plant's residual power.

462
00:35:39,650 --> 00:35:41,490
都是韩国科学家
Korean scientists,

463
00:35:42,690 --> 00:35:45,610
以及像我这样的外国核技术人员
foreign nuclear technicians like me.

464
00:35:45,700 --> 00:35:47,200
还有我们的一些家人
Some of our families too.

465
00:35:51,910 --> 00:35:55,870
掠夺者死光之前 杀死了我们大约一半的人 然后…
Marauders killed about half of us before they died out. And then--

466
00:35:55,960 --> 00:35:57,000
掠夺者 
Marauders?

467
00:35:57,920 --> 00:36:01,000
然后严寒或辐射中毒 夺走了其余人的性命
And then the cold or radiation poisoning took the rest of us.

468
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:04,420
我侄子当时是15岁
My nephew, he was 15 years old.

469
00:36:05,090 --> 00:36:06,720
他是最后一个死的
He was the last to go.

470
00:36:09,390 --> 00:36:10,930
他得了甲状腺癌
He had thyroid cancer.

471
00:36:12,770 --> 00:36:16,400
到最后 他在求我把他杀了
By the end, he was begging me to kill him.

472
00:36:17,770 --> 00:36:19,230
那是大约四年前的事了
That was about four years ago.

473
00:36:19,860 --> 00:36:20,820
在那之后…
After that…

474
00:36:22,610 --> 00:36:23,530
我…
I…

475
00:36:24,240 --> 00:36:25,400
我就没有了时间的概念
I lost time.

476
00:36:26,070 --> 00:36:28,070
不再抱有希望 不再去想
I stopped hoping, stopped thinking.

477
00:36:28,820 --> 00:36:32,290
除了我之外还有其他人住在那下面
It's like someone other than me lived down there.

478
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:36,670
然后我看见了你
Then I turned my eyes on you.

479
00:36:37,790 --> 00:36:39,420
我很抱歉地告诉你
I hate to tell you this,

480
00:36:39,500 --> 00:36:42,750
在你与世隔绝期间 人类并没怎么进化
but humankind hasn't exactly evolved in your absence.

481
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:48,010
你甘冒生命危险 甚至不顾理智 就为了救我
You pushed past what was safe, even sane, to rescue me.

482
00:36:50,010 --> 00:36:50,890
为什么 
Why?

483
00:36:55,850 --> 00:36:57,520
我很高兴自己那么做了
I'm just glad I did.

484
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:06,030
我们还是基本没有信号
We're still basically blind.

485
00:37:06,110 --> 00:37:07,950
我们上次到这里时还有卫星图像的
We had picture last time we came out here.

486
00:37:08,030 --> 00:37:10,780
-卫星信号在持续减弱 -说说其他选择
The satellites continue to degrade. - Options?

487
00:37:10,870 --> 00:37:12,280
等等 我们有其他选择 
- Wait, there's options?

488
00:37:13,370 --> 00:37:16,000
我们直接回到主轨道上
We go back directly to the main line,

489
00:37:16,710 --> 00:37:19,210
到时候 如果他们在我们前面 我们就会看到迹象
where we either see physical signs they're in front of us,

490
00:37:19,290 --> 00:37:21,080
不然 我们就知道他们在后面
or we know they're behind us.

491
00:37:21,170 --> 00:37:23,170
或者我们可以与主轨道平行前进
Or we parallel the main line,

492
00:37:23,250 --> 00:37:26,720
希望信号会变好 能让我们在卫星图像上探测到他们
hoping the signal improves enough so we can glimpse them on the sat.

493
00:37:28,930 --> 00:37:30,930
-选第二个方法 -遵命
- Second route. - Roger that.

494
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:45,530
你刚才那样决定的依据是什么 
And, um, you picked that based on what?

495
00:37:46,610 --> 00:37:47,820
又看到了未来 
Another vision?

496
00:37:48,570 --> 00:37:52,030
不是 不上主轨道 我们会有更多选择的余地 对吗 
No, I mean, there's gotta be more options off the main line, right?

497
00:37:53,490 --> 00:37:54,450
对
Yeah.

498
00:38:55,050 --> 00:38:57,680
她为我们牺牲了自己 所以现在我们得解除这玩意儿
She sacrificed for us. So now, we gotta kill this thing.

499
00:38:57,760 --> 00:39:00,140
-好吗  -这是笔记本电脑的连接口
- Okay? - The laptop patch is in here.

500
00:39:01,230 --> 00:39:02,890
所以没法黑入它的软件
So we can't hack the software.

501
00:39:04,900 --> 00:39:09,780
也许我们可以中断电源 扰乱它的供电
Maybe we can disrupt the power supply, mess with it.

502
00:39:13,610 --> 00:39:14,950
这好像是装载程序面板
Looks like an arming sequence.

503
00:39:23,710 --> 00:39:25,290
-它被激活了 -糟糕 
- It's live. - Oh, shit!

504
00:39:27,420 --> 00:39:29,630
-我觉得它处于全脉冲状态 -是 我看到了
- I think it's at full pulse. - I can see that.

505
00:39:29,710 --> 00:39:30,840
我没法把它关了
I can't turn it down.

506
00:39:32,090 --> 00:39:33,470
停不下来
It's not stopping.

507
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:37,640
好吧…
Well…

508
00:39:44,390 --> 00:39:48,860
我早知道会是一个 对铁路后勤具有敏锐洞察力的人
I knew it had to be someone with acumen for rail logistics.

509
00:39:49,520 --> 00:39:52,070
但老实说 更令我钦佩的是
But to be honest, I'm more impressed with how low you went

510
00:39:52,150 --> 00:39:54,150
你居然会如此屈尊 跟末等人混在一起
to grovel it out in the bowels.

511
00:39:55,490 --> 00:39:57,740
我在尽量不辜负期望 先生
Well, I do try not to disappoint, sir.

512
00:40:00,160 --> 00:40:01,870
如果你能保持忠诚该多好
If you'd only stayed loyal.

513
00:40:03,330 --> 00:40:04,370
我是忠诚的
I am loyal.

514
00:40:06,290 --> 00:40:09,540
我的忠诚给了比你更重要的东西 威尔福德先生 你全搞错了
To something bigger than you. You've got it all wrong, Mr. Wilford.

515
00:40:09,630 --> 00:40:12,510
这话我一直听到 但我还是赢了
I hear that all the time, and then I win.

516
00:40:12,590 --> 00:40:13,880
赢和领导是两回事
Winning isn't leading.

517
00:40:15,010 --> 00:40:16,640
光有忠诚还不够
Loyalty isn't enough on its own.

518
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:20,890
还需要有爱 不是你享受的那种敬畏之爱
It has to come with love. And not the kind that you feed off.

519
00:40:20,970 --> 00:40:24,600
而是无条件的爱 愿为每一个乘客牺牲
Unconditional love. Sacrifice, for each and every passenger.

520
00:40:24,680 --> 00:40:26,850
-老天  -你不能忽视爱的力量
- Oh, God! - You can't ignore love.

521
00:40:28,900 --> 00:40:30,520
你也无法预测它的力量
You can't predict it either.

522
00:40:34,150 --> 00:40:36,200
好吧 我们得把这玩意儿 送出那扇门去
We gotta get this thing out that door.

523
00:40:36,280 --> 00:40:38,910
-没有开门的密码 也没防护服 -我在想办法呢
- We don't have door codes or breach suits. - Uh, thinking. Uh…

524
00:40:40,490 --> 00:40:41,370
第二年那场叛乱
Year two rebellion.

525
00:40:41,450 --> 00:40:44,200
他们封了通勤车的门不让我们上 但我们弄坏了铰链
They sealed the subtrain doors on us, but we compromised the hinges.

526
00:40:44,290 --> 00:40:45,290
快去
Go.

527
00:40:45,370 --> 00:40:46,540
在这里
Here.

528
00:40:48,710 --> 00:40:50,420
强壮男孩 准备好
Strong Boy, get it ready.

529
00:40:57,430 --> 00:40:59,050
好 解除了 来吧
Okay. Clear. Come on.

530
00:41:00,550 --> 00:41:01,680
动手吧
Let's go.

531
00:41:05,270 --> 00:41:06,310
准备好了 
Ready!

532
00:41:06,390 --> 00:41:08,770
他们此刻正在为你准备门洞
They're preparing the port for you now.

533
00:41:10,560 --> 00:41:13,820
我会确保他们把臂铐放高夹紧
I'll make sure they mount the cuff nice and high

534
00:41:14,610 --> 00:41:16,900
让你将来没法装假肢
where prosthetics are impossible.

535
00:41:18,450 --> 00:41:20,030
反正我也不会戴假肢
Wouldn't wear one anyway.

536
00:41:25,540 --> 00:41:27,080
来吧 你好了吗 
Come on. You got it?

537
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:29,000
好 快跑 姐妹 快跑
Okay, run. Run, sister, run.

538
00:41:36,510 --> 00:41:37,470
快走
Go.

539
00:41:56,360 --> 00:41:59,400
讽刺的是 我当初建门洞 只是一种虚声恫吓
The irony is, I built the ports in as an idle threat.

540
00:41:59,490 --> 00:42:01,360
从没想过要使用它们
Never expected to use them.

541
00:42:02,530 --> 00:42:03,580
而你却用了
You did.

542
00:42:04,780 --> 00:42:06,450
13次
Thirteen times.

543
00:42:10,330 --> 00:42:11,370
我愿意赎罪
I'll pay my penance.

544
00:42:13,840 --> 00:42:14,840
把我的手臂冻掉吧
You can have my arm.

545
00:42:52,540 --> 00:42:54,250
我很好奇那会是什么
- Whoa. - Whoa.

546
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,090
是电磁波 
I wonder, what on earth could that be?

547
00:42:59,710 --> 00:43:01,050
正在三角定位
Electromagnetic?

548
00:43:01,130 --> 00:43:03,390
这是特征痕迹 一定是他们
Triangulating.

549
00:43:03,470 --> 00:43:04,300
没错 是他们
Well, that's the signature. It's gotta be them.

550
00:43:04,390 --> 00:43:06,600
在我们西侧520公里处
Yes, it is. Five hundred and twenty kilometers west.

551
00:43:06,680 --> 00:43:08,220
他们在主轨道上
They're on the main line.

552
00:43:08,310 --> 00:43:10,230
这比在卫星图像上找到他们强多了
That's a lot better than seeing them on sat.

553
00:43:10,310 --> 00:43:13,230
是吗 也就是说威尔福德看不到我们
Yeah? So it means Wilford can't see us.

554
00:43:14,150 --> 00:43:15,650
我们比他有优势
We got the drop on him.

555
00:43:15,730 --> 00:43:17,980
-威尔福德讨厌意外之事 -很好
- Well, Wilford hates surprises. - Good.

556
00:43:19,530 --> 00:43:20,740
我们去给他一个“惊喜”
Let's go give him one.

557
00:43:47,300 --> 00:43:49,140
我为你们做了一样东西
I built something for you.

558
00:43:52,020 --> 00:43:55,310
一样本可以挽救无数性命的东西
Something that would have saved countless lives.

559
00:43:57,020 --> 00:43:59,820
我们本可以不费一颗弹药
We could have snuffed out Layton's pirate train

560
00:43:59,900 --> 00:44:00,900
就毁掉雷顿的强盗列车
without firing a shot.

561
00:44:03,070 --> 00:44:06,280
如今 就因为一个
Now, thanks to a rat

562
00:44:07,950 --> 00:44:09,740
躲在管道中的叛徒
found hiding in the pipes,

563
00:44:10,990 --> 00:44:12,410
这场战争爆发时
when this war comes,

564
00:44:14,250 --> 00:44:15,540
你们将会有伤亡
you're all going to bleed.

565
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:24,130
都因为你 这场战争 又将回到原始的打斗方法
It's back to broadswords and shields because of you.

566
00:44:29,220 --> 00:44:30,390
先生 好了 随时可以行刑
Ready when you are, sir.

567
00:44:33,060 --> 00:44:34,810
那就冻断它吧
Let's get it bloody off then.

568
00:45:02,550 --> 00:45:05,170
他们回来了
They're back. They're back.

569
00:45:21,860 --> 00:45:23,780
-去战斗岗位  -快走 
- Battle stations! - Let's go!

570
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:26,570
去战斗岗位 狗崽子们 
Battle stations, you dogs!

571
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:29,700
快啊 
Come on!

572
00:45:53,010 --> 00:45:58,020
字幕翻译： 黛拉


